[Game is Unaware of Collosi (Useless)]
author=bungholio
description=With that the game seems unaware of any colossus near you. L1 doesn&#039;t target them, their health bar doesn&#039;t appear (I don&#039;t know if they can be killed because of that, didn&#039;t check), and I went into time trial and left the first colossus and when I hit the ground, I got that little movie pointing out where he was. Also the sword doesn&#039;t reflect light on it&#039;s weak spot.

I have 000000x0 written in my text file, so maybe it&#039;s specifically 012D9B58 00000000.
patch=1,EE,212D9B58,extended,00000000

[Have All Items Equipped]
author=bungholio
description=With that, all items from both normal and hard time trials are equipped at the same time. It&#039;s different than the Have all items code, because that just makes them available in the start menu. With this, they are all equipped. Your horse is also entirely white, and you also have the stick that you light on fire for that one colossus. Just make sure to press left, not right. For some reason the stick didn&#039;t want to appear when I pressed right. And I was lazy with this code, I didn&#039;t check what all the individual values do.
This code can freeze the game if you turn on the have all items code with it.
patch=1,EE,212DA3E0,extended,FFFFFFFF
patch=1,EE,212DA3E4,extended,FFFFFFFF

[Have Items In Pool Modifier]
author=bungholio
description=Add the bits together to get the items you want. Save your game, quit, and restart without the codes on. Then you can pick up all of your items and save to have them. The items are different depending on the game difficulty.

Item Bits:
000040 = Whistling Arrow (Normal) or Harpoon Of Thunder (Hard)
000100 = Cloak Of Force (Normal) or Sword Of The Sun (Hard)
000400 = Mask Of Strength (Normal) or Fruit Tree Map (Hard)
001000 = Lizard Detection Stone (Normal) or Shaman&#039;s Cloak (Hard)
004000 = Fruit Tree Map (Normal) or Lizard Detection Stone (Hard)
010000 = Mask Of Power (Normal) or Shaman&#039;s Mask (Hard)
040000 = Cloak Of Deception (Normal) or Cloth Of Desperation (Hard)
100000 = Flash Arrow (Normal) or Queen&#039;s Sword (Hard)
patch=1,EE,E001E264,extended,01358290
patch=1,EE,212D9B64,extended,00000040

[Have Items in the Pool Modifier]
author=bungholio
description=100000 = Flash Arrow (Normal)/Queen&#039;s Sword (Hard)
10000 = Mask of Power (Normal)/Shaman&#039;s Mask (Hard)
40000 = Cloak of Deception (Normal)/Cloth of Desperation (Hard)
1000 = Lizard Detection Stone (Normal)/Shaman&#039;s Cloak (Hard)
4000 = Fruit Tree Map (Normal)/Lizard Detection Stone (Hard)
100 = Cloak of Force (Normal)/Sword of the Sun (Hard)
400 = Mask of Strength (Normal)/Fruit Tree Map (Hard)
40 = Whistling Arrow (Normal)/Harpoon of Thunder (Hard)

When you start, all the items you unlock by beating the colossi in time trials will be in the pool. They are different depending on whether you play on normal or hard difficulty. There might be a side effect of the camera doing that thing where it zooms in on the pool about every 8 seconds if you have more than 1 item, I didn&#039;t check.

Specifically, the Harpoon of Thunder reacted differently than the other items. I didn&#039;t get that little movie where the camera zooms in on the pool, and when I picked it up the game didn&#039;t have that bit where the spirits tell you what the item is and what it does. I swung my sword to get out of the pose.
patch=1,EE,212D9B64,extended,00100000

